Have you listened to the latest #DearGabbyPoecast Big Talk with @jennadewan 🦋Tune in to Dear Gabby #16 at the link in bio @gabbybernstein and learn ...

> How to speak to your children to avoid codependent relationships
> The importance of not making your feelings your children’s problem
> The struggles of finding balance as a working parent
> How dance kept Jenna embodied and healed her trauma
> Ways to gain confidence in your body through movement and sexuality
> Methods to physically process and move shame through you
> Why it’s essential to help our daughters feel confident in their bodies
> The secret to shame-free parenting

Click the link in my bio @gabbybernstein or search for "Dear Gabby" anywhere podcasts are streamed.

#jennadewan #deargabby #gracefullyyou #connection #happiness #workingparents #shamefree #noshame #parenting #boundaries #selflove #spiritjunkie

I’m going to make meditation EASY, fun and something you become OBSESSED WITH! 

Here’s how:

I’m leading a Meditation Challenge!

Starting August 1 I’ll be your meditation coach for 21 days. 

You’ll get: 
21 daily meditations (different styles each day) 
Exclusive member platform and downloadable journal 
Daily emails to keep you on track (plus text support if you want) 
Community support (literally the coolest group ever!) 
A live training session with me on Day 21! 
Let me help you make meditation easy.

Link in bio @gabbybernstein 

The meditation challenge is perfect for you if you’re ready to … 

Stick to your meditation practice.
Learn to meditate or amp up your existing practice. 

Feel awesome! You’ll be amazed at how good it feels when you commit to a daily meditation practice. 

Attract more of what you want! When you feel good, you attract solutions, come up with inspired ideas and much, much more!

Get motivated—you can speed up by slowing down. 

Stop focusing on problems and attract solutions. Meditating daily will help you see spiritual guidance in everything around you.

Let’s do this! Join now at the link in bio @gabbybernstein

In this week's episode of Dear Gabby I teach one of the fastest ways to let go of control. It’s an old Dear Gabby method from 2006! 

This OG method is called the 3 Rs and it’s designed to help you rapidly process and release uncomfortable feelings in 90 seconds! 

The 3 Rs stands for Recognize, Record, Release.

It’s simple. All you need is to have a small journal on hand throughout the day. (Or you can use the Notes app in your iPhone.)

The next time you notice a negative controlling thought come up, do this:

Recognize: Notice the thought.
Record: Write it down in a journal.
Release: Say a prayer, “Thank you, Universe, for transforming this fear and helping me release it now.”

On the podcast I break this method down even further. (Link in bio)

node.text:
Do you struggle with catastrophic thoughts? 

Hare are three ways to redirect your thoughts in the moment and release anxiety. 

1. You can tell the thoughts to stop. Yup... Literally say out loud in your head "stop!" or "no!" These simple words interrupt the momentum of the negative thoughts. 

2. Ask yourself, "What's the best case scenario?" Thinking of a more positive outcome will redirect your thoughts onto what you do want, rather than spiraling out into thoughts of what you don't want. 

3. Repeat a positive affirmation to help you reconnect to the everpresent peace within you. Some examples include, I am safe, All is well, The Universe Has My Back. Give yourself permission to lean towards empowering affirmations to release the stronghold of anxiety. 

👉For more on this topic listen to my Dear Gabby podcast for guidance on how to practice good feeling thoughts and release anxiety. DearGabby.com
